  "name": "Chaotic Form",
  "desc": "You cause the form of a willing creature to become malleable, dripping and flowing according to the target’s will as if the creature were a vaguely humanoid-shaped ooze. The creature is not affected by difficult terrain, it has advantage on Dexterity (Acrobatics) checks made to escape a grapple, and it suffers no penalties when squeezing through spaces one size smaller than itself. The target’s movement is halved while it is affected by **chaotic form**.\n",
  "level": 4,
  "higher_level": "When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the duration increases by 10 minutes for each slot level above 4th.",
